"contrary to :func:`numpy.vecdot`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/linalg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.linalg.vecdot:7
msgid ""
"Let :math:`\\mathbf{a}` be a vector in ``x1`` and :math:`\\mathbf{b}` be a "
"corresponding vector in ``x2``. The dot product is defined as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/linalg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.linalg.vecdot:10
msgid ""
"\\mathbf{a} \\cdot \\mathbf{b} = \\sum_{i=0}^{n-1} \\overline{a_i}b_i\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/linalg/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.linalg.vecdot:13
msgid ""
"over the dimension specified by ``axis`` and where :math:`\\overline{a_i}` "
"denotes the complex conjugate if :math:`a_i` is complex and the identity "
"otherwise."
msgstr ""

